1
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:11,208
[NARRATOR] Shigeo Kageyama,
also known as Mob,

2
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:12,875
second year of middle school.

3
00:00:12,958 --> 00:00:14,583
[yawns]

4
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,291
[NARRATOR]
In one's life, the second year

5
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:19,958
of middle school kicks off
a most sensitive time.

6
00:00:20,041 --> 00:00:23,875
It is commonly
known as adolescence.

7
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:26,041
Some thrive in athletics.

8
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:28,333
Some work hard on their studies.

9
00:00:28,416 --> 00:00:30,916
Some devote themselves
to their hobbies.

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,333
Some polish their talents.

11
00:00:33,416 --> 00:00:35,958
Some rebel.

12
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:38,000
While some fall for
the opposite sex,

13
00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:42,000
tasting bittersweet, and
sometimes unrequited, love.

14
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:43,791
All those youthful desires form

15
00:00:43,875 --> 00:00:47,166
the amalgamation
that is adolescence.

16
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:50,125
And, what was Mob doing
during this precious time?

17
00:00:50,208 --> 00:00:54,625
Working as an assistant for
a psychic at 300 yen an hour.

18
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:57,833
The reason for your
curse is porn sites!

19
00:00:57,916 --> 00:01:00,125
Wait a second. Porn sites?

20
00:01:00,208 --> 00:01:01,583
Yes!

21
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:03,958
The jinx you carry on your
shoulders is a terrible one,

22
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:07,916
commonly referred to
as the One-Click Curse!

23
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:44,791
[CLIENT 2A]
A-A one-click curse contracted

24
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,000
from web porn?

25
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:48,500
They use illegal,
18-plus sites to curse

26
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:51,666
your shoulders while also
burdening you with their fees.

27
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,833
Nowadays, even
supernatural curses

28
00:02:53,916 --> 00:02:54,666
are being digitized.

29
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:56,166
[CLIENT 2A]
Get real!

30
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,708
Who in the hell would believe
that giant tub of hogwash?

31
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:01,958
Relax and keep perfectly still.
I'll lift the curse right now.

32
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,333
No, there's no need to go--!

33
00:03:03,416 --> 00:03:05,125
[grunts]

34
00:03:05,208 --> 00:03:06,750
Your right shoulder is stiff.

35
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:08,708
The curse really
has a hold on you.

36
00:03:08,791 --> 00:03:10,166
If you think I'm
payin' for this,

37
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,750
you've got another thing coming!

38
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:14,125
[CLIENT 2A grunting]

39
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:15,083
[CLIENT 2A]
What the--?

40
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:17,666
It actually feels pretty good!

41
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:18,500
[ARATAKA grunts]

42
00:03:18,583 --> 00:03:21,500
[ARATAKA]
Sorcery Crush!

43
00:03:21,583 --> 00:03:23,125
Finishing blow!

44
00:03:23,208 --> 00:03:26,000
[NARRATOR] This is one
of Reigen's special moves.

45
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:28,791
He relieves the stress
from physical fatigue,

46
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:32,708
and gets rid of stiff
shoulders and back pain.

47
00:03:32,791 --> 00:03:35,041
[sighs]

48
00:03:35,125 --> 00:03:37,458
I believe that I was
able to lift the curse.

49
00:03:37,541 --> 00:03:39,125
Do your shoulders
still feel heavy?

50
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,083
No! I'm sorry that
I doubted you.

51
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:42,833
Everything feels so much better!

52
00:03:42,916 --> 00:03:44,958
May I come again
for a follow-up?

53
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:46,958
That'd be no problem!

54
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:48,208
Let's see...

55
00:03:48,291 --> 00:03:51,500
The fee for a 40-minute
massage is 3,800 yen.

56
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:53,458
[ARATAKA] Idiot! Don't
call it a massage fee!

57
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:55,500
Call it the
"curse-dispelling" fee!

58
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:57,916
[MOB]
Two hundred yen is your change.

59
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,041
[ARATAKA]
Hey, here you go, Mob.

60
00:03:59,125 --> 00:04:00,291
Feelin' kinda hungry?

61
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:02,458
Yes. Thanks for the food.

62
00:04:03,625 --> 00:04:05,791
Master Reigen, you're
getting much better

63
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:07,333
at these massages, lately.

64
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:08,583
Well, yeah.

65
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,125
I've been tryin' different
things to improve,

66
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,041
like reading up on
some new techniques.

67
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:15,333
'Course, it's only effective
'cause of my spiritual power.

68
00:04:17,416 --> 00:04:18,791
Hot!

69
00:04:18,875 --> 00:04:20,208
Such a waste!

70
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,791
Master, I...

71
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:25,916
I've been thinking
about something...

72
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,916
Well, this is a rare occasion.

73
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,666
You don't start conversations.

74
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,208
[MOB]
Well...

75
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:33,791
I can use a little ESP, and I'm
different from other people,

76
00:04:33,875 --> 00:04:35,750
so I came to discuss
that with you

77
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:38,208
and then I ended up
becoming your student.

78
00:04:38,291 --> 00:04:40,125
At the time, I didn't
have anybody else

79
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:43,375
to talk to, so I was
and am grateful...

80
00:04:43,458 --> 00:04:47,291
Because you teach me things,
and pay me on top of it all.

81
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:49,250
However, I wonder...

82
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:51,083
Is this really okay?

83
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,875
That's what's been on my mind.

84
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:57,875
[ARATAKA]
Does he think his pay's too low?

85
00:04:57,958 --> 00:05:00,333
Or did he finally figure
out that I'm a fraud?

86
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:03,041
What do you mean exactly?

87
00:05:03,125 --> 00:05:04,916
How do I put this...

88
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,333
Rather than waste my youth
working after school,

89
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:10,125
I have this sneaking suspicion
that there are other things

90
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:12,166
I should be experiencing
in my life.

91
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,083
Huh?!

92
00:05:14,166 --> 00:05:15,958
Ah, so that's what
you're talkin' about!

93
00:05:16,041 --> 00:05:19,250
Puberty! An important
phase in one's life.

94
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:21,625
Is there something specific
you wanna do right now?

95
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:23,791
Be in a band? Dance?

96
00:05:23,875 --> 00:05:25,541
Hitchhike across the country?

97
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:28,875
No, I don't have anything
particular in mind.

98
00:05:28,958 --> 00:05:30,291
Okay. Listen, Mob.

99
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:31,666
I understand what
you're going through,

100
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,750
but there's no need
to rush into things.

101
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,791
In my opinion,
the Going-Home Club

102
00:05:35,875 --> 00:05:37,041
is what's best.

103
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,500
You're goofin' off
during the period

104
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,375
of your life you can
goof off the most,

105
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:42,625
and that makes you
a winner in my book.

106
00:05:42,708 --> 00:05:44,750
So, I say, just keep
on bein' a slacker

107
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:48,000
and make money off me. Ya know?

108
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,041
[INUGAWA]
Now, hold on a second, Takenaka!

109
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:51,250
[TAKENAKA]
I get treated like a weirdo

110
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:53,000
just for being in
this stupid club!

111
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:54,125
[INUGAWA]
Take it easy!

112
00:05:54,208 --> 00:05:56,500
I can't do it anymore!

113
00:05:56,583 --> 00:05:57,500
[INUGAWA groans]

114
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:58,875
This isn't good.

115
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:01,750
A club's supposed have
five or more members, right?

116
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:04,250
So what should we
do now, President?

117
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,375
There's only one
thing we can do.

118
00:06:06,458 --> 00:06:08,666
We've gotta find a new member.

119
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,125
And I mean now!

120
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:13,291
[knocking]

121
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:15,375
Maybe Takenaka changed
his mind and came back.

122
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:18,041
That's gotta be it! Takenaka!

123
00:06:18,125 --> 00:06:19,458
[ALL gasp]

124
00:06:19,541 --> 00:06:20,875
[TOKUGAWA]
I just received a submission

125
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:22,916
of resignation from this club.

126
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,791
It's...

127
00:06:23,875 --> 00:06:25,666
[ALL]
The student council!

128
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,583
This club... is abolished.

129
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:28,583
Abolished?

130
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:29,916
Wow! Already?!

131
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,708
Sadly, I'm going to
have to ask you

132
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,250
to gather your things.

133
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:35,833
I recently had a
brand-new club request

134
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:37,250
for a room just like this.

135
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:38,291
Hold on!

136
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:39,250
We've only been down
to four members

137
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,666
for a few minutes!

138
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,625
I'm not gonna let you get
rid of the Telepathy Club!

139
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:45,041
The bond we share in
this Club's too strong!

140
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:46,958
The student council's
got nothing on us!

141
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,333
You think you're all
high and mighty

142
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:49,916
because of how you
part your hair?!

143
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,250
Shut your mouths.

144
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:53,583
You pissants don't really
wanna anger me, do you?

145
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:55,000
[ALL whimper]

146
00:06:55,083 --> 00:06:56,083
If you're that desperate

147
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,041
to keep this joke
of a club going...

148
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,708
...then bring me
a brand new member

149
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:02,708
by the end of the
school day on Friday.

150
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:05,541
[INUGAWA]
B-By Friday? For real?

151
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:07,541
That only gives us two days.

152
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:08,916
Impossible.

153
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,458
[sighs]

154
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:11,458
Quit your whining!

155
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:13,000
If we ask everyone
we see to join,

156
00:07:13,083 --> 00:07:15,041
we'll be able to
snag at least one!

157
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:16,416
But, that's not
gonna happen, now.

158
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,666
The recruiting season
ended a long time ago.

159
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,708
[TOME]
No! I'm gonna let this go!

160
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:22,958
We haven't overcome
obstacle after obstacle

161
00:07:23,041 --> 00:07:26,208
to be shot down in such
a ridiculous way, have we?!

162
00:07:26,291 --> 00:07:28,375
[ALL]
Uh, president?

163
00:07:28,458 --> 00:07:31,708
We haven't done
a single thing.

164
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:34,000
[school bell rings]

165
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:36,166
[ALL panting]

166
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:38,625
I didn't even know this school
had a Telepathy Club.

167
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,250
It's creepy, so forget it.

168
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:41,500
Nah, I've got a job, guys.

169
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,500
What's the big deal?

170
00:07:42,583 --> 00:07:43,916
If it's abolished,
it's abolished.

171
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,166
You should be studying.
Entrance exams are this year.

172
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:48,000
Well, are any guys
in your club hot?

173
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,708
[ALL panting]

174
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,250
I wanna leave time for dating.

175
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,916
I'd be worried about the stares,
and it seems too dangerous.

176
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,333
It's creepy, so forget it.

177
00:07:55,416 --> 00:07:57,083
Sorry. It's creepy,
so forget it.

178
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:58,375
It's creepy, so forget it.

179
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,750
[ALL panting, groaning]

180
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:01,333
Creepy.

181
00:08:01,416 --> 00:08:01,791
Nope.

182
00:08:01,875 --> 00:08:02,166
Forget it.

183
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,041
Uh, no.

184
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,500
[STUDENT 2P]
Sounds lame. No.

185
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:09,375
Guess it really is impossible

186
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:11,833
to find new members
this time of year.

187
00:08:11,916 --> 00:08:14,666
Not to mention we keep
getting called "creepy."

188
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:17,416
Now even I wanna quit.

189
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,166
[TOME gasps]

190
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:21,125
[screams]

191
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:22,500
[KIJIBAYASHI]
The president's lost it!

192
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:24,500
[SARUTA]
You need to calm down, okay?!

193
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:27,791
[gasps] The Going-Home Club...

194
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:30,041
[INUGAWA]
President!

195
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,083
I found him!

196
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:32,333
He's not in any
clubs or committees,

197
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,041
and he doesn't have any
friends or girlfriends.

198
00:08:34,125 --> 00:08:35,625
Salt's go-homer
and all-round bum,

199
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:37,791
Shigeo Kageyama of
Year 2, Class 1.

200
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:39,875
Well, I'd say he's
basically right.

201
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:41,291
Well done, Inukawa!

202
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:43,916
Please allow me introduce
you to the other members:

203
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,791
Kijibayashi, and Saruta.

204
00:08:45,875 --> 00:08:46,791
Nice to meet you.

205
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:47,916
How's it goin'?

206
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,750
And I'm the president
of this group,

207
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:51,875
Tome Kurata, Year 3, Class 5.

208
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:54,208
You can call me
All-The-Way Tome.

209
00:08:57,291 --> 00:08:59,166
[INUGAWA]
She's pulling out all the stops!

210
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,791
Tome, huh? Hey,
what a coincidence!

211
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,291
That's my grandmother's name.

212
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:05,916
Uh-- See? The fates
have brought us together!

213
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,125
There you have it!

214
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:08,875
Please join the Telepathy Club!

215
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:09,833
I can't today.

216
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,291
What?!

217
00:09:11,375 --> 00:09:12,375
Wait just a second, Mob!

218
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:14,416
Are you serious?
You actually have plans?

219
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:15,750
[MOB]
Mm-hm. I have to head out

220
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:18,208
to my after-school
exorcism job right now.

221
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:20,750
Exorcism? What is that
supposed to mean?

222
00:09:20,833 --> 00:09:21,666
Ah! President!

223
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,041
I just remembered something!

224
00:09:23,125 --> 00:09:25,375
This guy was sort of famous
back in grade school!

225
00:09:25,458 --> 00:09:27,541
He could bend spoons
and make erasers move.

226
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,250
You know, like telekinesis!

227
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,541
In other words, he's an esper!

228
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:34,375
Stop being such a weirdo
and just join our club.

229
00:09:34,458 --> 00:09:37,333
I mean, the exorcism can wait
a little while, right?

230
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,875
[phone ringing]

231
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,875
Mob. Hey, so how's
it goin' with you?

232
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:44,166
[MOB]
Uh, Master...

233
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,291
I'm being recruited into a club.

234
00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:47,916
Is it okay if I'm a little late?

235
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,916
Just join and leave,
what's the big deal.

236
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,375
No, I have to wait until
the student council meeting

237
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:54,916
is over, then go submit
my club admission form.

238
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,125
Wait.

239
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:57,500
So if I told you to come
to work immediately,

240
00:09:57,583 --> 00:09:59,041
you'd end up not joining?

241
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,291
Uh, yeah, but...

242
00:10:00,375 --> 00:10:02,208
Shouldn't I try and keep
the promise I made

243
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,708
to the others first?

244
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:05,583
[ARATAKA] Then, it's not like
you actually want to join?

245
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,250
[MOB]
Not really, no.

246
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,625
'Kay, hurry on over.

247
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,208
Time for you to show 'em
how things are done

248
00:10:10,291 --> 00:10:11,708
in the Going-Home Club.

249
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:14,583
He says he needs me right
away, so I'll be going now.

250
00:10:14,666 --> 00:10:16,333
[TOME]
P-Put me on for a sec!

251
00:10:16,416 --> 00:10:18,375
Look, I really need
Kageyama to join today

252
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,125
no matter what, understand?!

253
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:23,375
[ARATAKA] A girl, huh?
She must be trying to use Mob.

254
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:26,083
He's not really the type to
play any kind of sports stuff.

255
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:27,833
Probably isn't a good
idea to force him.

256
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,625
[TOME] We're not some
stupid sports club!

257
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:31,000
We're the Telepathy Club!

258
00:10:31,083 --> 00:10:32,625
Huh? You're kidding me.

259
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:35,250
It's a club where we train
to feel telepathic powers.

260
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:37,250
Uh, that sounds shady as hell.

261
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,375
"Telepathic," huh?

262
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:39,541
Don't play dumb with me!

263
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:41,250
You know exactly what
I'm talking about!

264
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,416
I've heard from a reliable
source that Kageyama

265
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,125
has telekinesis and ESP!

266
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,166
I bet you're just
using him to solve cases

267
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,708
and get more customers
'cause you can't do it

268
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:50,250
