285
00:11:19,916 --> 00:11:21,875
Trust me, they just don't
wanna lose their room,

286
00:11:21,958 --> 00:11:23,041
their budget,

287
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:24,875
and their pointless
after-school time,

288
00:11:24,958 --> 00:11:27,291
judging from what their
club sounds like to me.

289
00:11:27,375 --> 00:11:29,166
See through it, Mob!

290
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:30,875
If that shady club goes down,

291
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,708
it's because it was damn
well meant to go down.

292
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:36,375
If you understand,
hurry up and come to work!

293
00:11:36,458 --> 00:11:39,125
I get it. See you soon.

294
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,875
So, it looks like I gotta go.

295
00:11:40,958 --> 00:11:43,083
Sorry about that.
I'll catch you guys later.

296
00:11:43,166 --> 00:11:44,708
[INUGAWA]
Uh-- Wait a sec!

297
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:46,791
Please, just hear me out, okay?!

298
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:48,541
Now listen, the
president seriously

299
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:50,458
believes in telepathy
and all that stuff,

300
00:11:50,541 --> 00:11:51,875
but honestly,
the rest of us here

301
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:54,166
just wanna lie
around and goof off.

302
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,791
Right now, we're
in middle school.

303
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:57,291
This is the only time
we're gonna be able

304
00:11:57,375 --> 00:11:59,833
to do nothing and
get away with it!

305
00:11:59,916 --> 00:12:01,333
Play cards with us in this lazy

306
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:04,666
little paradise we've
created! What do ya say?

307
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:07,416
You're not gonna find a more
carefree club than this.

308
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,666
We have until tomorrow
to set things straight,

309
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:11,875
so think it over?

310
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:14,375
You're our last hope, Kageyama!

311
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:15,708
Save us!

312
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:17,500
[MOB]
Mm...

313
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,583
[ARATAKA] So I assume you
turned them down, didn't ya?

314
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:22,625
Nuh-uh. I figured I'd take
a night to think about it.

315
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:25,666
[ARATAKA] You shouldn't
drag these things out, Mob.

316
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,000
[WOMAN 2A] I know, I couldn't
believe it myself when he--

317
00:12:27,083 --> 00:12:28,875
You need to turn down
things you don't wanna do.

318
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:31,541
